original: Josefsson, Carl Johan, teol. o. fil. kand., läroverksadjunkt, Falkenberg, f. 2/10/92 i Söndrum, Hall. 1., av kvarnäg. Josef Johansson o. Benedik- ta Svensson. G. 36 m. Märta Strand. Barn: Gunhild f. 37, Carl-Erik 38. — Stud:ex. i Halmstad 11, stud. v. Gbgs liögsk. 11, v. Lunds univ. 12, teol. fil. ex. 13, teol. kand. 16, fil. kand. 18, provår 21. Res. t. Tyskl. 28 o. 30. E. lär. i Skellefteå 18-20 o. 21-22, adj. där 22, adj. i kristend. o. modersm. v. Falkenbergs samrealsk. sed. 31. RVO 44.
translated: Josefsson, Carl Johan, Bachelor of Theology and Philosophy, high school teacher, Falkenberg, b. 2/10/92 in Söndrum, Halland, eldest son of mill owner Josef Johansson and Benedikta Svensson. Married in 1936 to Märta Strand. Children: Gunhild b. 1937, Carl-Erik b. 1938. He passed his studentexamen (school leaving exam) in Halmstad in 1911 and studied at Gothenburg University from 1911-1912 and Lund University in 1912. He passed the theology and philosophy exam in 1913, the theology degree in 1916, the philosophy degree in 1918 and worked as a teacher in Skellefteå from 1918 to 1922. He was appointed as an adjunct teacher of Christianity and Swedish language at Falkenberg's lower secondary school in 1931. He traveled to Germany in 1928 and 1930. Awarded RVO (Knight of the Royal Order of Vasa) in 1944.
